<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="468" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1158,1363]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1158,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is rare in the Lurenzgriecht (
<tableCitation box="[757,829,1158,1183]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,239,472,495]" captionTargetBox="[156,1342,618,1591]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Species inventory of water mites found in the Lurenzgriecht 1999 – 2009 in systematic order. Results from benthic and interstitial samplings (Gerecke et al. 2005 and own unpublished samplings) are given separated from the presence of the species in the emergence traps (only 2002). o = lacking in the emergence traps, x = present, (x) = rare; only single specimens." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF236659F53EFFD9FF6CFE2FD9CBC826" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" tableUuid="DF236659F53EFFD9FF6CFE2FD9CBC826">Tab. 1</tableCitation>
) and at the present time there is only a fragmentary description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Efford" box="[317,471,1194,1219]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" refString="Efford, I. E. (1966) The larvae of Feltria romijni. Acarologia, 8 (3), 456 - 459." type="journal article" year="1966">Efford (1966)</bibRefCitation>
without any morphometric measurements and one illustration in 
<bibRefCitation author="Martin" box="[1203,1365,1194,1219]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" refString="Martin, P. (1998) Zur Autokologie der Wassermilben (Hydrachnidia, Acari) zweier norddeutscher Tieflandbache. Ph. D. thesis, University of Kiel, 269 pp." type="book" year="1998">Martin (1998)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1158,1363]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">
Two characters seem to enable a separation of the two species: in 
<taxonomicName box="[950,1036,1231,1254]" class="Arachnida" family="Feltriidae" genus="Feltria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rouxi">
<emphasis box="[950,1036,1231,1254]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">F. rouxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the separation of the coxal plates I and II (nearly to the median margin of the common plate) is more extended than in 
<emphasis box="[1149,1251,1268,1291]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">F. m ot as i</emphasis>
(the separation reaches only the level of seta C1). But obviously some metric characters are also different, e.g., a long seta 
<date box="[1346,1381,1303,1327]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">
V 
<quantity box="[1367,1381,1303,1327]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" unit="in" value="4.0">4</quantity>
</date>
in 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Feltriidae" genus="Feltria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rouxi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">F. rouxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(about 100µm: 
<bibRefCitation author="Muller" box="[389,531,1338,1363]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" refString="Muller, H. (2015) Morphologie, Taxonomie und Parasitismus einiger Wassermilbenlarven und einer Nymphe (Acari: Hydrachnidia) in der Saale (Thuringen). Lauterbornia, 80, 69 - 111." type="journal article" year="2015">Müller 2015</bibRefCitation>
; Müller &amp; Martin, in prep.) in contrast to a short one in 
<taxonomicName box="[1159,1277,1340,1363]" class="Arachnida" family="Feltriidae" genus="Feltria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setigera">
<emphasis box="[1159,1277,1340,1363]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">F. setigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(&lt;50µm).
</paragraph>
